				<h3>Messiah College</h3>

				<p>I want to express my thanks to the many people at <a class="links" href="http://www.messiah.edu/site/index.php" target = "_blank">Messiah College</a>
					who have in one way or another supported my mycological endeavors over the last few decades as I sought to
					deepen my experience with macroscopic fungi rather than the	microscopic pathogens I studied so much in graduate school.
				</p>

				<p>Thanks are extended to Dr. Jeffrey Moshier, Dr. Ray Norman, Dr. Angela Hare
					<a class="links" href="http://www.messiah.edu/info/20198/school_of_science_engineering_and_health">
						(Deans of the School of Science, Engineering and Health)</a>,
					and Dr. Gerald Hess and Dr. Sheri Boyce (Chairs of the
					<a class="links" href="http://www.messiah.edu/info/20200/department_of_biological_sciences">Department of Biological Sciences)</a>
					for their support of this project in the form of release time.
				</p>

				<p>Special thanks are also extended to Les Weiand, former Assistant Director of Academic Computing,
					who patiently explained Dreamweaver and Fireworks, the software used to construct the original web site in 2006.
				</p>

				<p>My appreciation is extended to Ken Mark,
					Director of the <a class="links" href="http://www.messiah.edu/Oakes/">Oakes Museum of Natural History</a>,
					for providing the Oakes Museum web site as a home for this web site.
				</p>

				<p>For the past several years I have collaborated with Dr. Scott Weaver and students in his CIS 432,
					Database Applications class in order to transform the existing version of my website employing
					dichotomous keys and static web pages to a database-driven website utilizing multi-access keys
					and dynamically created pages. The 2016 team of students who accomplished this transformation are Von Bock,
					Emily Budd, Z-Ean Chung, Kafui Dzaka, Huey Hum, and Hoang Nguyen.I am very thankful to Dr. Weaver and his students for this collaborative relationship.
				</p>
			</div>

