				</p>

				<p><strong>Pam Kaminski -</strong> Pam is an amateur mycologist and photographer and a member of Eastern Penn Mushroomers.</p>

				<p><strong>Dr. Rosalind Lowen -</strong> Roz is a former Honorary Research Associate of the Institute of Systematic Botany
					at the New York Botanical Garden. She is retired and now lives in NH.
					he has done research on fungi that occur on lyme disease ticks, fungi that occur on lichens,
					and she has been an analyst of fungi in the air and in buildings.
				</p>

				<p><strong>Dr. Steve Nelsen -</strong> Steve is an organic chemist at University of Wisconsin, Madison, WI.
